YOOX controls the use of yoox.com users' personal data; YOOX autonomously determines the purposes and means of use, including security measures, for the protection of personal data. For organizational and operational purposes only, we have appointed certain entities that will also process personal data belonging to yoox.com's users, such purposes which are strictly connected to the performance of services on yoox.com, including the sale of products.

The above mentioned processors have been chosen by YOOX because of their experience in processing personal data and they provide sufficient guarantees in respect of compliance with data processing law (including the technical security measures governing the processing to be carried out). In processing the personal data of yoox.com's users, the processors shall act only on instructions from YOOX. We regularly ensure that our processors comply with our instructions and that they provide sufficient guarantees on their full compliance with the provisions on personal data processing.

Some of the processors of your personal data are: YOOX ASIA Ltd, a subsidiary of YOOX S.p.A., having an address at GFL, 2nd FL, 3rd FL 16th FL, Western Plaza, No. 3 San On Street and No. 2 Tin Hau Road, Tuen Mun, N.T., Hong Kong ("YOOX ASIA"). We provide YOOX ASIA, by electronic and papers means, with customers' address and other personal data for the purpose of performing the agreements entered into between Users (who browse and/or purchase products from this Site) and YOOX;
United Parcel Service, for purposes relevant to shipping and delivering products purchased on yoox.com;
BT Italia S.p.A. for purposes relevant to the housing of YOOX servers.

Please contact our Customer Care or send us an e-mail at privacy@yoox.com if you would like to receive a full list of our data processors.

You are entitled to obtain, at any time, confirmation from YOOX as to whether or not data relating to you is being processed, whether the data is not yet registered, and the communication in intelligible form of the data undergoing processing.

Moreover, you are entitled to receive from YOOX information on the source of your personal data; the purposes and way of processing your personal data; the logic involved in any electronic data processing; details of the data controller and of the data processors and the names of subjects and categories of subjects to whom your personal data may be disclosed or who may access your personal data like, for example, the names of data processors. You can easily find all of the above information in our Privacy Policy.

You are entitled to obtain at any time from YOOX:

a) the updating, rectification or, when you have an interest in, the integration of your personal data;
b) the deletion, the transformation into an anonymous form or blocking of your personal data, (unlawful processed), including data which does not need to be stored for the purposes for which it has been collected and subsequently processed;
c) the confirmation that the operations under letters a) and b) have been reported, (together with the contents of the same), to whom the data was disclosed or disseminated, except when it becomes impossible or if it means exceeding the protection of the relevant right.

You are entitled to object, in all or in part:

a) for legitimate reasons, to the processing of your personal data, even if it is related to the purposes for which it was collected;
b) to the processing of your personal data for advertising or direct marketing purposes or in order to carry out marketing researches or commercial communications.

You may freely and at any time exercise your rights, provided that you do so in compliance with applicable laws, by sending your request to YOOX at the following e-mail address privacy@yoox.com. We will reply to you in order to satisfy your request.
